sentiment_score_definition: x <= -0.35: Bearish; -0.35 < x <= -0.15: Somewhat-Bearish; -0.15 < x < 0.15: Neutral; 0.15 <= x < 0.35: Somewhat_Bullish; x >= 0.35: Bullish
relevance_score_definition: 0 < x <= 1, with a higher score indicating higher relevance.

feed.title: Progyny Q4 2025 Earnings Preview: Revenue Slowdown Anticipated - News and Statistics
feed.summary: Progyny is preparing to report its Q4 2025 earnings, with analysts anticipating a slowdown in revenue growth to 3.3% year-on-year, compared to 10.6% in the prior year's same quarter. The company has previously missed Wall Street's revenue estimates multiple times in the last two years, contrasting with competitors like CVS Health and Cigna who recently exceeded expectations. Progyny's stock has underperformed the sector, dropping 16.3% over the last month, and its current share price is significantly below the average analyst price target.

feed.title: Itaú Unibanco (ITUB) Stock Climbs to $9.33 on Record ROE, Digital Gains After Q4 2025 Beat
feed.summary: Itaú Unibanco's stock (ITUB) rose to $9.33, driven by a record return on equity, successful digital transformation, and a new share buyback program. The Brazilian banking giant reported strong Q4 and full-year 2025 results, with recurring managerial net income up 13.2% year-over-year and ROE hitting 23.4%. Analysts maintain a "Buy" rating, anticipating sustained performance despite macro risks.

feed.title: [8-K] CHESAPEAKE UTILITIES CORP Reports Material Event | CPK SEC Filing - Form 8-K
feed.summary: Chesapeake Utilities Corporation (CPK) reported strong financial results for 2025, with GAAP net income of $140.3 million and diluted EPS of $5.97, and adjusted net income of $141.1 million and adjusted EPS of $6.01, representing approximately 12% year-over-year earnings growth. The company invested a record $470.4 million in capital in 2025 and reiterated its 2024-2028 capital expenditure guidance of $1.5-$1.8 billion, along with a 2028 EPS target of $7.75-$8.00. Chesapeake Utilities also provided 2026 capital expenditure guidance of $450-$500 million, focusing on regulated distribution, transmission, infrastructure, unregulated businesses, and technology projects.

feed.title: Freightos Limited Ordinary shares (NASDAQ:CRGO) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
feed.summary: Freightos Limited (NASDAQ: CRGO) discussed its Q4 2025 earnings, revealing a primary focus on achieving profitability by the end of 2026 through disciplined growth and a "solutions-first" strategy. The company emphasized strengthening its SaaS solutions in air, ocean, and tendering, aiming to embed its offerings deeper into customer workflows to drive transaction growth and improve unit economics. Despite softer solutions revenue in 2025 due to longer sales cycles, Freightos expects revenue growth of 6% to 12% in 2026 and aims for adjusted EBITDA breakeven by Q4.

feed.title: Delcath Systems Reports Fourth Quarter and Full Year 2025 Results
feed.summary: Delcath Systems announced strong financial results for Q4 and the full year 2025, reporting total revenue of $20.7 million and $85.2 million respectively, with positive non-GAAP adjusted EBITDA. The company also highlighted significant growth in HEPZATO KIT procedure volume and successful publication of clinical study results supporting its therapies. Looking ahead to 2026, Delcath expects total CHEMOSAT and HEPZATO KIT revenue to reach at least $100 million due to continued site activations and commercial expansion.

feed.title: KeyCorp Draws Takeover Interest As Scale And Franchise Value Come Into Focus
feed.summary: First Citizens BancShares Inc. is reportedly considering an acquisition of KeyCorp, which would merge two regional U.S. banks amidst ongoing sector consolidation. This potential interest highlights KeyCorp's significant scale and diverse operations, making it an attractive target for a buyer aiming to exceed the US$250 billion asset threshold. Investors are now watching for formal proposals and the terms of any potential deal, as the situation remains fluid.

feed.title: Elliott Pressure Puts Norwegian Cruise Line Overhaul And Valuation In Focus
feed.summary: Activist investor Elliott Investment Management has launched a campaign targeting Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings (NYSE:NCLH), urging significant board and leadership changes, along with a revamp of capital allocation strategies concerning private island investments and ship deployment. This push comes as the company experiences recent CEO and board turnover and mixed stock performance. Investors will need to monitor how the new leadership responds to Elliott's demands and if changes are made to impact the company's long-term risk and opportunity profile.

feed.title: NRDC investor briefing warns Sempra’s Vista Pacífico LNG project faces high financial and reputational risk
feed.summary: A new investor briefing from NRDC warns that Sempra’s proposed Vista Pacífico LNG export project in Sinaloa carries significant financial, legal, and reputational risks for investors. The analysis highlights market headwinds, potential stranded assets due to shifting global decarbonization, tightening methane regulations, and severe biodiversity and community-rights concerns in the Gulf of California. NRDC advises investors to reassess their exposure before these issues lead to costly delays or stranded assets.

feed.title: Abbott’s US$20b Bond Bet Recasts Growth Story In Oncology Diagnostics
feed.summary: Abbott Laboratories is acquiring cancer diagnostics company Exact Sciences, financed by a US$20 billion bond sale, marking its entry into the high-growth oncology diagnostics market. This strategic move aims to expand Abbott's presence in cancer testing and screening, but also introduces significant balance sheet and integration risks. Investors should monitor the integration process, impact on net profit margins due to increased interest expenses, and how Abbott competes with peers in this new segment.

feed.title: Sempra Is Up 16%. Here’s How Much the Stock Could Rise by 2026
feed.summary: Sempra stock has climbed 16% over the past six months, driven by improving regulatory visibility and strong institutional buying. A valuation model suggests the stock could rise by 15% to $108, indicating it is modestly undervalued. This potential upside is supported by projected revenue growth, stable operating margins, and strategic infrastructure investments, particularly with an anticipated regulatory approval for its Oncor affiliate.

feed.title: Carrier Introduces AquaEdge 30CF Chiller to Enhance Data Center Reliability and Uptime
feed.summary: Carrier has launched the AquaEdge® 30CF air-cooled centrifugal chiller, designed to significantly improve reliability and uptime for data centers. This new chiller, part of the Carrier QuantumLeap™ portfolio, is engineered to operate across extreme temperatures, restore full cooling capacity within three minutes of a power interruption, and minimize maintenance through its magnetic bearing technology. It aims to address the growing demands of AI and high-performance computing by providing robust and integrated thermal management solutions.

feed.title: TE Connectivity plc (TEL) Positioned for AI-Driven Growth Amid Strong Order Book
feed.summary: TE Connectivity plc (NYSE: TEL) is strengthening its financial position with a new $3 billion senior revolving credit facility, replacing a previous $1.5 billion one. The company is well-positioned to benefit from the surge in demand for AI-related tools and products, driven by increased investment in data centers and network equipment. TE Connectivity reported strong Q1 fiscal 2026 orders exceeding $5 billion and revenues above expectations, with optimistic guidance for Q2 adjusted profit.

feed.title: Parker-Hannifin (PH) Accelerates Synergies with Strategic Acquisitions
feed.summary: Parker-Hannifin (NYSE: PH) presented at Citi’s Global Industrial Tech & Mobility Conference, highlighting strong aerospace growth, industrial order recovery, and operational excellence driven by strategic acquisitions like Meggitt and the pending Filtration Group acquisition. The company reported double-digit aerospace growth for the fourth consecutive year and anticipates adjusted EBITDA margins near 28% for fiscal 2026, with industrial margins reaching record levels. These achievements underscore its leadership in motion and control technologies and its successful "Win Strategy" in various global markets.

feed.title: MGM RESORTS & BETMGM COMMIT OVER $1 MILLION TO RESPONSIBLE GAMING INITIATIVES DURING PROBLEM GAMBLING AWARENESS MONTH
feed.summary: MGM Resorts International and BetMGM have announced an expanded commitment of over $1 million towards responsible gaming initiatives during Problem Gambling Awareness Month. This commitment includes $450,000 for new research on sports wagering and its impact on player behavior, alongside significant contributions to state and national organizations focused on problem gambling prevention and treatment. The companies will also enhance their GameSense engagement program, employee training, and launch a new "Earn More. Play Smart." campaign to promote responsible play.

feed.title: American Express to build 55-floor tower at World Trade Center site

feed.title: Johnson & Johnson Medtech launches new CereGlide aspiration catheters in US
